books.Title: The Bible. That is, the Holy Scriptures, etc.
books.Book Notes:
There are multiple hands in this text dating from the early seventeenth century through to the late eighteenth. This includes hands that I cannot assign to agents, instances of secretary hand, and initials corresponding to the names of the original owner's sons. There are two female agents here with the same name and so I have designated them 'Susanna Beckwith (1)' and 'Susanna Beckwith (2)' to differentiate. They have distinct hands that make me reasonably certain that they correspond to different women, but some initials are hard to assign. Pagination begins again in each section (Old Testament, Apocrypha and New Testament) so I have designated pages as OT 1r, NT 1r or Apocrypha 1r, for example. 

There is a provenance note on the rear pastedown written by Arthur Onslow in 1768 that reads: "This Family Bible was my mother’s and she highly valued it. She was the daughter of Thomas Anlaby of Etton, Esq. and owner of Anlaby, both in Yorkshire, not far from Hull, and her mother was a daughter of Wm Parker M.D. and Judith a Daughter of Roger Beckwith of the said county esq. and of Susanna his wife which Susanna was the person that wrote the words at the end of the Apocrypha in this book, to her eldest daughter by the said Roger Beckwith, who was named Susanna, and afterwards married to John Anlaby Esq. by whom she had the above mentioned Thomas Anlaby, so that my mother was Great Grand Daughter to the here first mentioned Susanna by father and mother.". Marginalia also signed 'TA' on NT fol. 1r reads "Bequeathed to me by my deare Grandmother Susanna Beckwith TA", which I reasonably believe to be the Thomas Anlaby mentioned in the note by Arthur Onslow.
